Barely 24 hours after the senator representingB BauchiNorth Senatorial District of the state, Adamu Mohammed Bulkachuwa was suspended from the APC, a faction of the party at the state level announced the suspension of the state chairman, Uba Nana. Some aggrieved members of the party during a press conference yesterday accused Mr Nana of gross misconduct, describing his continued stay in office as illegal. A stalwart of the party, Ibrahim Ago, who addressed the press in Bauchi
accused the former governor of the state MA Abubakar of “illegally
leading a fraudulent election that produced the current leadership of
the party.” He said the current set of leaders of the APC under the leadership of
Uba Nana were responsible for the failure of the party during the
2019 elections. He said the processes that produces the leadership of Bauchi APC in
the state was faulty, adding that “we have decided to dismiss them and
appoint Malam Aminu Na-Borno as an interim Chairman pending when
election will be conducted to get the full leadership of the party.” Mr Ago also accused Uba Nana of romancing with the PDP
administration in Bauchi State. Also commenting, Rabiu Shehu Dan-Baba who introduced himself as the
chairman of the APC in Bauchi LGA, described Uba Nana, the state APC
chairman as “inept and lacking the leadership qualities to lead the
APC in Bauchi State, hence his dismissal as the State Chairman.” Responding, the APC chairman in Bauchi State, Uba Nana, described the
suspension as illegal.